 243: 
 244: ## 3. Phase 1 — v1.2: Critical Fixes
 245: 
 246: **Duration**: 8 weeks  
 247: **Goal**: Make `ign run` actually work for the vast majority of Docker Hub images. Make the system production-safe at the privilege level. Make the daemon crash-safe.
 248: 
 249: ### 3.1 CMD / ENTRYPOINT / ENV Support in Ignitefile + OCI Bridge
 250: 
 251: **Crate**: `ignite-core` (oci.rs, layers.rs) + `crates/ignited` (vm startup path)  
 252: **Priority**: P0 — highest impact fix in the entire project
 253: 
 254: #### 3.1.1 What to Build
 255: 
 256: When `ign pull <image>` or `ign build` runs, extract the OCI image config JSON and persist it alongside the ext4 rootfs. When `ign run` starts a VM, inject the config values as a small init wrapper.
 257: 
 258: #### 3.1.2 Implementation
 259: 
 260: **Step 1**: Extend the OCI client in `ignite-core/src/oci.rs` to parse the image config blob.
 261: 
 262: ```rust
 263: // ignite-core/src/oci.rs
 264: 
 265: #[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
 266: pub struct OciImageConfig {
 267:     /// e.g. ["/usr/sbin/nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]
 268:     pub entrypoint: Option<Vec<String>>,
 269:     /// e.g. ["-c", "/etc/nginx/nginx.conf"]
 270:     pub cmd: Option<Vec<String>>,
 271:     /// e.g. ["PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin", "PORT=8080"]
 272:     pub env: Option<Vec<String>>,
 273:     /// Working directory inside the VM
 274:     pub working_dir: Option<String>,
 275:     /// Exposed ports metadata (informational only)
 276:     pub exposed_ports: Option<HashMap<String, serde_json::Value>>,
 277:     /// User to run as (informational, used to set up init script)
 278:     pub user: Option<String>,
 279: }
 280: 
 281: impl OciImageConfig {
 282:     /// Produce the full command to exec: ENTRYPOINT + CMD combined
 283:     pub fn full_command(&self) -> Vec<String> {
 284:         let mut cmd = vec![];
 285:         if let Some(ep) = &self.entrypoint {
 286:             cmd.extend_from_slice(ep);
 287:         }
 288:         if let Some(c) = &self.cmd {
 289:             cmd.extend_from_slice(c);
 290:         }
 291:         if cmd.is_empty() {
 292:             cmd.push("/bin/sh".to_string());
 293:         }
 294:         cmd
 295:     }
 296: }
 297: ```
 298: 
 299: **Step 2**: After layer flattening, write `ignite-config.json` into the image cache directory.
 300: 
 301: ```
 302: ~/.ignite/images/<image-hash>/
 303:     rootfs.ext4       # Read-only base image
 304:     ignite-config.json  # NEW: parsed OCI config
 305:     manifest.json
 306: ```
 307: 
 308: **Step 3**: In `crates/ignited/src/vm_manager.rs`, before calling the Firecracker boot API, generate `/sbin/ignite-init` inside the VM's rootfs COW layer and set it as the kernel `init=` boot parameter.
 309: 
 310: ```rust
 311: // crates/ignited/src/vm_manager.rs
 312: 
 313: fn generate_init_script(config: &OciImageConfig) -> String {
 314:     let mut script = String::from("#!/bin/sh\n");
 315:     
 316:     // Inject environment variables
 317:     if let Some(env_vars) = &config.env {
 318:         for var in env_vars {
 319:             // var is "KEY=VALUE"
 320:             script.push_str(&format!("export {}\n", var));
 321:         }
 322:     }
 323:     
 324:     // Set working directory
 325:     if let Some(wd) = &config.working_dir {
 326:         script.push_str(&format!("cd {}\n", wd));
 327:     }
 328:     
 329:     // Exec the actual command (ENTRYPOINT + CMD)
 330:     let full_cmd = config.full_command();
 331:     let exec_line = full_cmd.iter()
 332:         .map(|s| shell_escape(s))
 333:         .collect::<Vec<_>>()
 334:         .join(" ");
 335:     script.push_str(&format!("exec {}\n", exec_line));
 336:     
 337:     script
 338: }
 339: 
 340: /// Inject /sbin/ignite-init into the COW layer before VM boot.
 341: /// We use debugfs to write the script without mounting the filesystem.
 342: fn inject_init_script(cow_path: &Path, config: &OciImageConfig) -> Result<()> {
 343:     let script = generate_init_script(config);
 344:     let script_path = temp_file_with_content(&script)?;
 345:     
 346:     // Write script into ext4 image via debugfs (no mount required, no root needed)
 347:     Command::new("debugfs")
 348:         .args(["-w", cow_path.to_str().unwrap()])
 349:         .stdin(format!("write {} /sbin/ignite-init\nchmod 0755 /sbin/ignite-init\n", 
 350:                        script_path.display()))
 351:         .status()?;
 352:     
 353:     Ok(())
 354: }
 355: ```
