1519: ### 5.3 Teleport — Live VM Migration
1520: 
1521: **Crate**: `crates/ignite-teleport/`  
1522: **Priority**: P2 — flagship feature
1523: 
1524: #### 5.3.1 Protocol Overview
1525: 
1526: Pre-copy memory migration protocol:
1527: 
1528: ```
1529: Source Node                              Destination Node
1530: -----------                              ----------------
1531: 1. Mark all memory pages as "dirty"      1. Allocate memory buffer
1532:    via KVM_GET_DIRTY_LOG ioctl
1533:    
1534: 2. Bulk copy ALL pages over WireGuard    2. Write pages to buffer
1535:    overlay network
1536:    
1537: 3. Repeat: copy only dirty pages         3. Receive dirty pages
1538:    (pages written since last round)      
1539:    Iterate until dirty rate < threshold
1540:    
1541: 4. Pause VM (VMCL: pause call to         4. Receive final delta
1542:    Firecracker /pause)                   
1543:    
1544: 5. Copy final dirty pages + CPU state   5. Reconstruct VM memory
1545:    (Firecracker snapshot files)         
1546:    
1547: 6. Notify destination: "start VM"       6. Load snapshot into new
1548:                                            Firecracker instance
1549:    
1550: 7. Update overlay network routing       7. VM resumes
1551:    (VM IP now routes to dest node)
1552: 
1553: 8. Destroy source VM
1554: ```
1555: 
1556: #### 5.3.2 Source Node Implementation
1557: 
1558: ```rust
1559: // crates/ignite-teleport/src/sender.rs
1560: 
1561: use kvm_ioctls::{Kvm, VmFd};
1562: 
1563: pub struct MigrationSender {
1564:     vm_fd: VmFd,
1565:     fc_client: FirecrackerClient,
1566:     wg_stream: TcpStream,   // WireGuard-encrypted stream to destination
1567: }
1568: 
1569: impl MigrationSender {
1570:     pub async fn migrate(
1571:         mut self,
1572:         vm_id: &str,
1573:         dest_addr: SocketAddr,
1574:     ) -> Result<MigrationStats> {
1575:         let total_pages = self.vm_fd.get_num_pages()?;
1576:         let page_size = 4096u64;
1577:         
1578:         // Phase 1: Enable dirty tracking
1579:         self.vm_fd.enable_dirty_log()?;
1580:         
1581:         // Phase 2: Initial bulk transfer
1582:         let initial_dirty = self.get_all_pages()?;
1583:         self.send_pages(&initial_dirty).await?;
1584:         
1585:         // Phase 3: Iterative refinement
1586:         let mut round = 0;
1587:         loop {
1588:             let dirty = self.get_dirty_pages()?;
1589:             let dirty_count = dirty.count_ones() as u64;
1590:             
1591:             tracing::debug!("Migration round {}: {} dirty pages", round, dirty_count);
1592:             
1593:             if dirty_count < MIGRATION_THRESHOLD_PAGES {
1594:                 break;  // Dirty rate low enough to do final pause
1595:             }
1596:             
1597:             self.send_pages_by_bitmap(&dirty).await?;
1598:             round += 1;
1599:         }
1600:         
1601:         // Phase 4: Final pause + snapshot
1602:         self.fc_client.pause_vm().await?;
1603:         
1604:         // Send final dirty pages
1605:         let final_dirty = self.get_dirty_pages()?;
1606:         self.send_pages_by_bitmap(&final_dirty).await?;
1607:         
1608:         // Send Firecracker snapshot (CPU state)
1609:         let snap = self.fc_client.create_snapshot().await?;
1610:         self.send_snapshot(snap).await?;
1611:         
1612:         // Signal destination to resume
1613:         self.send_signal(MigrationSignal::Resume).await?;
1614:         
1615:         // Update routing in Swarm overlay
1616:         update_vm_routing(vm_id, dest_addr).await?;
1617:         
1618:         Ok(MigrationStats { rounds: round + 1, total_pages })
1619:     }
1620:     
1621:     fn get_dirty_pages(&self) -> Result<BitVec> {
1622:         // KVM_GET_DIRTY_LOG ioctl
1623:         self.vm_fd.get_dirty_log(0, todo!("slot size"))
1624:             .map(|bitmap| BitVec::from_vec(bitmap))
1625:             .map_err(Into::into)
1626:     }
1627: }
1628: ```
